description:
Field Day

When Midge decides to play the field for awhile, Archie decides that he'd like to try it, too! But that might be a little more difficult for him that he thinks... n>

Why Me?

Though it may be hard to believe, the actions of one person can make a huge difference in a community. It's up to us whether that impact is a positive one or a negative one!

Power Mad

Archie's new mini-bike is really cool, but they're not street legal, so he can't ride it anywhere! When Veronica offers to let him burn rubber in the Lodge indoor gym, though, there's bound to be trouble!

The Sleeper

Who knew that Riverdale's favorite redhead was such a talented surfer?! Not us, not Betty or Veronica -- not even Archie himself!

Who Scent Him

Mr. Lodge stinks! He's trying out his company's new cologne line, but they haven't been too successful yet. Can a certain carrot-top come up with the winning formula?

Changing Times

Pop Tate's Chocklit Shoppe is a Riverdale fixture, but it might not be for long! His business has been floundering, and kids aren't coming in as much as they used to. Can Archie and the boys help him out by giving the place a facelift?

The Long Long Week

Sometimes the only thing that gets you through the week is the promise of the weekend! That definitely holds true for the students of Riverdale High. For all their complaining, what is it that they have planned for this Saturday..?

Mr. Svenson spends an awful lot of time cleaning the floors of Riverdale High -- especially when it's snowy and slushy outside! People keep tracking dirt all over his freshly-cleaned hallways! Will he be able to make the chore a little more fun before he starts mopping up the students?

Turning Over a New Leaf?

Archie is determined to finally win Mr. Weatherbee's favor! He's got a few ideas on how to butter him up -- but will that work, or will it only raise suspicion?

Sign Bored

Reggie must have just taken a penmanship class, because his latest pranks involve making signs and hanging them up for Archie to see! Can Archie find a way to keep from falling for his tricks, or has Reggie won this round?

The Natural Thing

Archie is so accident-prone that Mr. Lodge doesn't even notice anymore! Archie's offended -- but he's having an awfully hard time proving to him that it's not true!

Waste Not Want Not

Mr. Lodge gives the gang a lesson on water pollution during a fishing trip, and it's got them thinking. Can they clean up the channel?

Choice Location

The public beach is no place for a Lodge -- or at least that's what Veronica says. But since she promised Archie and Betty, she'll have to go. Nobody said she couldn't go in style, though!

The Choice

Archie and Ronnie have a date tonight, but when he hears that Jughead's in danger of getting mugged by a rival at the same time, he'll have to make a choice! Will he risk incurring Veronica's wrath to save his buddy?

So What's New?

Archie's on a mission to arrive at school on time! But it's mostly because he's going to get a majorly bad detention if he's late! Can he keep from getting distracted long enough to make it?

Missionary Impossible

The air pollution in Riverdale is getting to be excessive, and Archie's going nuts trying to stop it! Can he make his voice heard?

The Helping Hand

There's a nasty little kid on the prowl today -- and he happens to be Veronica's little cousin! She doesn't believe Archie's claims that the kid's a terror, though. Will she see the light?

Success At Last

That skunk Reggie keeps stealing Archie's gifts for Veronica and giving them to her himself! When Arch keeps getting outsmarted, it's up to Jughead to give the prankster his just desserts.

Art Smart

Archie and Jughead can't seem to take modern art seriously. Are the girls seeing something that they're not?

Adventureland

Archie and Chuck are on the lookout for a kid who has run away from home! Can they use their acting skills and scare him straight?

Age Before Duty

Ms. Bettylou Clutchgrapple is the newest substitute teacher in Riverdale High, and she's absolutely gorgeous. Of course, this has turned most of the male population of Riverdale High into a bunch of drooling zombies! They don't even notice that she's not a good teacher -- but Betty and Veronica do! Can they get the word out, or will their pleas fall on deaf ears?

Temptation

It's the holiday season, and Reggie's rotten reputation is still going strong! But is there something that can break his mean streak?

The Rising Son

One of the most challenging things about going to school is actually waking up to go! Archie has trouble even standing up in the morning without drifting off again. Will his parents find a way to get him up in the morning?
name: Have you ever seen anything go as fast as these iceboats ?

description:
Clubs Are Trumps

Archie is carrying around an antique war club, and the girls don't trust him with it (for obvious reasons!) But would Riverdale's darling redhead really bonk someone like that?!

Here's The Pitch

Arch and Jughead are tossing pennies against the wall and seeing who can have it land closest! But Mr. Weatherbee comes down hard on them. What's got him so ticked off?

The Final Curtain

Archie has gotten so into his part in the school play that he won't take his costume off! But his showboating is about to get really annoying, really fast!

Roughing It

Archie and Jughead are taking a camping trip, and they're only bringing absolute essentials. You know, like rope, bug spray, caviar, bunny slippers...

Robinson Gruesome

You've heard of Robinson Crusoe, right? Famous story about a shipwrecked hero? Yeah, this isn't about him. This is Robinson Gruesome, a much more confused adventurer, and his fellow castaway who has figured out the secret to good living miles away from civilization...

Sandman

Archie's meeting the girls at the beach! But he forgot his sandals, and the sand is HOT! Can he make his way there without burning his feet off?

The Brush Off

Archie is painting the shed today, and he hasn't messed anything up yet! That is until Jughead and Reggie arrive on the scene...

Farmer's Daughter

When Archie drives his jalopy straight into a pond by a farm, they try to get a nearby bull to help pull them out! Will they be successful -- and will the bull's owner appreciate what they're doing?

Barrel of Fun

Ronnie is going bananas for Reggie's new barrel-jumping tricks! Archie won't take that lying down, so he's out to one-up his rival!

Race Against Time

Mr. Lodge has to submit some very important document to the Riverdale Town Hall offices by noon today, but the snowstorm outside has made the task nearly impossible! Luckily(?), there's a certain redhead who seems to have a knack for moving through the heavy snow...

The Mysterious Spot - A dark spot appears at Riverdale High, which allows its possessor to move through walls.

Lil Jinx - On Edge

Archie's Gag Bag

Anchors Away - Archie meets the father of Cindy Miller, an ex-admiral.

Archie Club News

A Workin' Fool - Archie tries to talk his way out of doing a task for his father.
